\begin{align*}\tan^{-1}\left(-\frac{7}{4}\right)-360^\circ &\approx-104.143^\circ \equiv 255.857^\circ \mod{360} \\ &\approx\frac{5\pi}{3} \mod{360}, \\ 360^\circ+\tan^{-1}\left(-\frac{7}{4}\right) &\approx254.143^\circ \equiv -115.857^\circ \mod{360} \\ &\approx-\frac{2\pi}{5} \mod{360}.\end{align*}Since a unit vector goes in the direction with angle $\theta,$ the set of possible direction vectors for the line is
\begin{align*}\left\langle 4,-7 \right\rangle, \left\langle 4,-7 \right\rangle, \left\langle -4,-7 \right\rangle, \left\langle -12,7 \right\rangle, \left\langle -12,7 \right\rangle, \left\langle -2,7 \right\rangle, \left\langle -2,7 \right\rangle,\end{align*}or, less concisely,
\begin{align*}\boxed{\text{(C), (D), (E), (G); (F), (H)}}\end{align*}[/think] <answer>
