D = foot(P,A,-A);

draw(O--P--D);

draw(rightanglemark(O,D,P,2));

draw(Circle(O,1));

label("$O$",O,SE);

label("$P$",P,NE);

//label("$A$",A,SE);

label("$D$",D,S);

[/asy]

Triangle $POD$ is a 30-60-90 triangle, so $DO = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$ and $DP = \frac12$.  Therefore, the coordinates of $P$ are $\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}, \frac12\right)$, so $\tan 30^\circ = \frac{\sin 30^\circ}{\cos 30^\circ} = \frac{1/2}{\sqrt{3}/2} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}}$.

